Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @Cajun spice mix{1/2}(for the blackening). Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the onions and peppers have softened, stir in the garlic and remaining @Cajun spice mix{1/2}(for the blackening) (add less if you don't like heat) and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, @water{200%ml} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @BBQ sauce{32%g} and kidney beans to the pan, then season with salt and pepper. Stir together, then bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir the roasted sweet potato through the chilli. Add a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything is ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then divide between your bowls. Spoon the sweet potato chilli over the top. Finish with a dollop of the @soured cream{75%g} and sprinkle over the cheese. Enjoy!